#: ../../source/concepts/authentication.rst:2
msgid "Authentication"
msgstr "Authentification"

#: ../../source/concepts/authentication.rst:4
msgid ""
"Nexus Gateway supports multiple authentication mechanisms and can enforce"
" them independently per route. Authentication is handled at the gateway "
"level, so backend services receive only verified requests."
msgstr ""
"Nexus Gateway prend en charge plusieurs mécanismes d'authentification et "
"peut les appliquer indépendamment par route. L'authentification est gérée "
"au niveau de la passerelle, de sorte que les services backend ne reçoivent "
"que des requêtes vérifiées."

#: ../../source/concepts/authentication.rst:9
msgid "Supported Authentication Methods"
msgstr "Méthodes d'authentification prises en charge"

#: ../../source/concepts/authentication.rst:12
msgid "API Keys"
msgstr "Clés API"

#: ../../source/concepts/authentication.rst:14
msgid ""
"API key authentication is the simplest method supported by Nexus Gateway."
" Clients include a key in the request header, and the gateway validates "
"it against a configured key store."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/authentication.rst:18
msgid ""
"By default, the gateway reads the key from the ``X-API-Key`` header. This"
" header name is configurable per route."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/authentication.rst:21
msgid ""
"API keys are suitable for server-to-server integrations where the client "
"environment is controlled and the key can be stored securely."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/authentication.rst:25
msgid "JWT Authentication"
msgstr "Authentification JWT"

#: ../../source/concepts/authentication.rst:27
msgid ""
"Nexus Gateway can validate JSON Web Tokens issued by any compatible "
"identity provider. The gateway verifies the token signature, expiry, and "
"configurable claims before forwarding the request."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/authentication.rst:31
msgid ""
"Supported signing algorithms are ``RS256``, ``RS384``, ``RS512``, "
"``ES256``, and ``HS256``. The public key or JWKS endpoint is configured "
"in the route definition."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/authentication.rst:48
msgid "OAuth 2.0 Token Introspection"
msgstr "Introspection de jeton OAuth 2.0"

#: ../../source/concepts/authentication.rst:50
msgid ""
"For deployments using an external authorisation server, Nexus Gateway "
"supports OAuth 2.0 token introspection. The gateway calls the "
"introspection endpoint with the bearer token and grants or denies the "
"request based on the response."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/authentication.rst:54
msgid ""
"This method adds latency because each request requires a call to the "
"authorisation server. Use response caching to reduce the impact on high-"
"traffic routes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/authentication.rst:59
msgid "How Authentication Failures Are Handled"
msgstr "Gestion des échecs d'authentification"

#: ../../source/concepts/authentication.rst:61
msgid ""
"When a request fails authentication, Nexus Gateway returns a ``401 "
"Unauthorized`` response. The response body contains a JSON error object "
"with a machine-readable error code and a human-readable message."
msgstr ""
"Lorsqu'une requête échoue à l'authentification, Nexus Gateway renvoie une "
"réponse ``401 Unauthorized``. Le corps de la réponse contient un objet "
"d'erreur JSON avec un code d'erreur lisible par machine et un message "
"lisible par un humain."

#: ../../source/concepts/authentication.rst:73
msgid ""
"The ``request_id`` field is included in all error responses and can be "
"used to trace the request in the gateway logs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/authentication.rst:77
msgid ""
"Do not expose detailed authentication error messages to end users in "
"production. Use the ``error`` code in your client application to display "
"appropriate user-facing messages, and log the full response server-side."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/authentication.rst:82
msgid "Combining Authentication with Authorisation"
msgstr "Combiner authentification et autorisation"

#: ../../source/concepts/authentication.rst:84
msgid ""
"Authentication confirms who the client is. Authorisation determines what "
"the client is allowed to do. Nexus Gateway handles both."
msgstr ""
"L'authentification confirme l'identité du client. L'autorisation détermine "
"ce que le client est autorisé à faire. Nexus Gateway gère les deux."

#: ../../source/concepts/authentication.rst:87
msgid ""
"After a successful authentication check, the gateway can evaluate "
"authorisation policies based on token claims, API key metadata, or "
"request attributes such as HTTP method and path."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/authentication.rst:91
msgid ""
"Authorisation policies are defined separately from authentication "
"configuration and can be reused across multiple routes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/rate-limiting.rst:2
msgid "Rate Limiting"
msgstr "Limitation de débit"

#: ../../source/concepts/rate-limiting.rst:4
msgid ""
"Rate limiting controls how many requests a client can make to a route "
"within a defined time window. Nexus Gateway enforces rate limits at the "
"gateway level, before requests reach backend services."
msgstr ""
"La limitation de débit contrôle le nombre de requêtes qu'un client peut "
"envoyer à une route dans une fenêtre de temps définie. Nexus Gateway "
"applique ces limites au niveau de la passerelle, avant que les requêtes "
"n'atteignent les services backend."

#: ../../source/concepts/rate-limiting.rst:9
msgid "Why Rate Limiting Matters"
msgstr "Pourquoi la limitation de débit est importante"

#: ../../source/concepts/rate-limiting.rst:11
msgid ""
"Without rate limiting, a single misbehaving client — whether due to a "
"bug, misconfiguration, or deliberate abuse — can consume enough resources"
" to degrade service for all other clients."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/rate-limiting.rst:15
msgid "Rate limiting protects your infrastructure by:"
msgstr "La limitation de débit protège votre infrastructure en :"

#: ../../source/concepts/rate-limiting.rst:17
msgid "Preventing individual clients from overwhelming backend services."
msgstr "Empêchant les clients individuels de saturer les services backend."

#: ../../source/concepts/rate-limiting.rst:18
msgid "Reducing the impact of denial-of-service attacks."
msgstr "Réduisant l'impact des attaques par déni de service."

#: ../../source/concepts/rate-limiting.rst:19
msgid "Enforcing usage quotas for clients on different pricing tiers."
msgstr "Appliquant des quotas d'utilisation pour les clients sur différents niveaux tarifaires."

#: ../../source/concepts/rate-limiting.rst:20
msgid "Smoothing out traffic spikes caused by batch jobs or retry storms."
msgstr "Lissant les pics de trafic causés par des traitements par lot ou des tempêtes de relance."

#: ../../source/concepts/rate-limiting.rst:23
msgid "How Nexus Gateway Counts Requests"
msgstr "Comment Nexus Gateway compte les requêtes"

#: ../../source/concepts/rate-limiting.rst:25
msgid ""
"Nexus Gateway uses a **sliding window** algorithm by default. The window "
"moves continuously rather than resetting at fixed intervals, which "
"prevents bursts of traffic at window boundaries."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/rate-limiting.rst:29
msgid ""
"A fixed window option is also available for use cases where predictable "
"reset times are required, such as billing-cycle quota enforcement."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/rate-limiting.rst:33
msgid "Rate Limit Identifiers"
msgstr "Identifiants de limite de débit"

#: ../../source/concepts/rate-limiting.rst:35
msgid ""
"Rate limits are applied per identifier. The identifier determines how the"
" gateway groups requests for counting purposes. Supported identifiers "
"are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/rate-limiting.rst:38
msgid ""
"**IP address** — limits requests from a single IP. Useful as a baseline "
"protection layer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/rate-limiting.rst:40
msgid ""
"**API key** — limits requests per authenticated client. The most common "
"approach for API products."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/rate-limiting.rst:42
msgid ""
"**JWT claim** — limits requests based on a value from the token payload, "
"such as a ``sub`` or ``org_id`` claim."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/rate-limiting.rst:44
msgid ""
"**Header value** — limits requests based on any request header. Useful "
"for custom client identification schemes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/rate-limiting.rst:47
msgid ""
"Identifiers can be combined. For example, you can apply both a per-IP "
"limit and a per-API-key limit to the same route. Both limits are enforced"
" independently."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/rate-limiting.rst:52
msgid "Rate Limit Response Headers"
msgstr "En-têtes de réponse de limite de débit"

#: ../../source/concepts/routing.rst:2
msgid "Request Routing"
msgstr "Routage des requêtes"

#: ../../source/concepts/routing.rst:4
msgid ""
"Routing is the process of matching an incoming request to a backend "
"service and forwarding it. In Nexus Gateway, routing rules are defined as"
" a list of routes in the configuration file. The gateway evaluates routes"
" in order and forwards the request to the first matching route."
msgstr ""
"Le routage est le processus qui consiste à faire correspondre une requête "
"entrante à un service backend et à la transmettre. Dans Nexus Gateway, les "
"règles de routage sont définies sous forme de liste de routes dans le "
"fichier de configuration. La passerelle évalue les routes dans l'ordre et "
"transmet la requête à la première route correspondante."

#: ../../source/concepts/routing.rst:10
msgid "Route Matching"
msgstr "Correspondance de routes"

#: ../../source/concepts/routing.rst:12
msgid ""
"Each route defines one or more match conditions. A request must satisfy "
"all conditions on a route to be considered a match."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/routing.rst:30
msgid "Route Priority"
msgstr "Priorité des routes"

#: ../../source/concepts/routing.rst:32
msgid ""
"Routes are evaluated in the order they appear in the configuration file. "
"The first route that matches the incoming request is used. Subsequent "
"routes are not evaluated."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/routing.rst:36
msgid ""
"This means more specific routes should be defined before broader ones. "
"For example, a route matching ``/api/v1/users/admin`` exactly should "
"appear before a route matching the ``/api/v1/users`` prefix."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/routing.rst:51
msgid ""
"If these routes were reversed, requests to ``/api/v1/users/admin`` would "
"be matched by the prefix route first and routed to the wrong upstream."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/routing.rst:55
msgid "Upstream Configuration"
msgstr "Configuration de l'amont"

#: ../../source/concepts/routing.rst:57
msgid ""
"Each route must specify an upstream — the backend service address to "
"which matching requests are forwarded."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/routing.rst:60
msgid "Nexus Gateway supports three upstream formats:"
msgstr "Nexus Gateway prend en charge trois formats d'amont :"

#: ../../source/concepts/routing.rst:62
msgid ""
"**Host and port** — ``orders-service:8080`` — for services reachable by "
"hostname within the same network."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/routing.rst:64
msgid ""
"**IP address and port** — ``10.0.1.15:3000`` — for services referenced by"
" IP."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/routing.rst:66
msgid ""
"**URL** — ``https://api.partner.example.com`` — for external upstreams or"
" when TLS is required on the upstream connection."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/routing.rst:70
msgid "Load Balancing"
msgstr "Équilibrage de charge"

#: ../../source/concepts/routing.rst:72
msgid ""
"When a route's upstream resolves to multiple instances — for example, via"
" DNS round-robin or a service registry integration — Nexus Gateway "
"distributes traffic across them using a configurable load balancing "
"strategy."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/routing.rst:76
msgid "The available strategies are:"
msgstr "Les stratégies disponibles sont :"

#: ../../source/concepts/routing.rst:78
msgid ""
"**Round robin** (default) — requests are distributed evenly across all "
"healthy instances in rotation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/routing.rst:80
msgid ""
"**Least connections** — each new request is sent to the instance with the"
" fewest active connections."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/routing.rst:82
msgid ""
"**IP hash** — the client IP address is hashed to select an instance, "
"ensuring that requests from the same client consistently reach the same "
"upstream. Useful for stateful applications."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/routing.rst:87
msgid "Health Checks"
msgstr "Vérifications de santé"

#: ../../source/concepts/routing.rst:89
msgid ""
"Nexus Gateway performs periodic health checks against upstream instances."
" Instances that fail a health check are removed from the routing pool "
"until they recover."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/routing.rst:93
msgid ""
"Health checks are configured per upstream and support both HTTP and TCP "
"probe types."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/routing.rst:97
msgid ""
"If all instances of an upstream fail their health checks simultaneously, "
"Nexus Gateway returns a ``503 Service Unavailable`` response to clients "
"until at least one instance recovers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/what-is-nexus-gateway.rst:2
msgid "What is Nexus Gateway?"
msgstr "Qu'est-ce que Nexus Gateway ?"

#: ../../source/concepts/what-is-nexus-gateway.rst:4
msgid ""
"Nexus Gateway is an open-source API gateway designed for teams running "
"microservice architectures. It acts as a single entry point for all "
"client requests, handling cross-cutting concerns such as authentication, "
"rate limiting, and request routing before traffic reaches your backend "
"services."
msgstr ""
"Nexus Gateway est une passerelle API open-source conçue pour les équipes "
"travaillant avec des architectures de microservices. Elle constitue un point "
"d'entrée unique pour toutes les requêtes clients, gérant des préoccupations "
"transversales telles que l'authentification, la limitation de débit et le "
"routage des requêtes avant que le trafic n'atteigne vos services backend."

#: ../../source/concepts/what-is-nexus-gateway.rst:9
msgid "Nexus Gateway architecture diagram"
msgstr "Schéma d'architecture de Nexus Gateway"

#: ../../source/concepts/what-is-nexus-gateway.rst:13
msgid "*The Nexus Gateway sits between clients and your backend services.*"
msgstr "*Nexus Gateway s'intercale entre les clients et vos services backend.*"

#: ../../source/concepts/what-is-nexus-gateway.rst:16
msgid "Core Responsibilities"
msgstr "Responsabilités principales"

#: ../../source/concepts/what-is-nexus-gateway.rst:18
msgid ""
"An API gateway is responsible for tasks that would otherwise need to be "
"implemented individually in every service. Nexus Gateway centralises "
"these concerns so your services can focus on business logic."
msgstr ""
"Une passerelle API est responsable de tâches qui devraient autrement être "
"implémentées individuellement dans chaque service. Nexus Gateway centralise "
"ces préoccupations afin que vos services puissent se concentrer sur la "
"logique métier."

#: ../../source/concepts/what-is-nexus-gateway.rst:22
msgid "The main responsibilities of Nexus Gateway are:"
msgstr "Les principales responsabilités de Nexus Gateway sont :"

#: ../../source/concepts/what-is-nexus-gateway.rst:24
msgid ""
"**Traffic routing** — directing incoming requests to the correct backend "
"service based on path, headers, or other request attributes."
msgstr ""
"**Routage du trafic** — direction des requêtes entrantes vers le bon service "
"backend en fonction du chemin, des en-têtes ou d'autres attributs de requête."

#: ../../source/concepts/what-is-nexus-gateway.rst:26
msgid ""
"**Authentication and authorisation** — verifying the identity of clients "
"and enforcing access policies before requests reach your services."
msgstr ""
"**Authentification et autorisation** — vérification de l'identité des clients "
"et application des politiques d'accès avant que les requêtes n'atteignent "
"vos services."

#: ../../source/concepts/what-is-nexus-gateway.rst:28
msgid ""
"**Rate limiting** — protecting backend services from traffic spikes and "
"abuse by controlling how many requests a client can make over a given "
"period."
msgstr ""
"**Limitation de débit** — protection des services backend contre les pics de "
"trafic et les abus en contrôlant le nombre de requêtes qu'un client peut "
"effectuer sur une période donnée."

#: ../../source/concepts/what-is-nexus-gateway.rst:30
msgid ""
"**Request and response transformation** — modifying headers, query "
"parameters, or payloads in transit when needed."
msgstr ""
"**Transformation des requêtes et des réponses** — modification des en-têtes, "
"des paramètres de requête ou des charges utiles en transit si nécessaire."

#: ../../source/concepts/what-is-nexus-gateway.rst:32
msgid ""
"**Observability** — collecting metrics, logs, and traces across all "
"incoming traffic from a single point."
msgstr ""
"**Observabilité** — collecte des métriques, journaux et traces de l'ensemble "
"du trafic entrant depuis un point unique."

#: ../../source/concepts/what-is-nexus-gateway.rst:36
msgid "How Nexus Gateway Fits Into Your Architecture"
msgstr "Comment Nexus Gateway s'intègre dans votre architecture"

#: ../../source/concepts/what-is-nexus-gateway.rst:38
msgid ""
"In a typical deployment, Nexus Gateway runs at the edge of your "
"infrastructure, directly behind your load balancer or ingress controller."
" All external traffic passes through the gateway before reaching any "
"internal service."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/what-is-nexus-gateway.rst:42
msgid ""
"This placement gives you a consistent enforcement layer for security and "
"operational policies without modifying individual services."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/what-is-nexus-gateway.rst:45
msgid ""
"Nexus Gateway is stateless by design. Configuration is defined in a YAML "
"file or via the Admin API, and the gateway reads this configuration at "
"startup or when a reload is triggered."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/what-is-nexus-gateway.rst:50
msgid "When to Use Nexus Gateway"
msgstr "Quand utiliser Nexus Gateway"

#: ../../source/concepts/what-is-nexus-gateway.rst:52
msgid "Nexus Gateway is a good fit if your team:"
msgstr "Nexus Gateway est adapté si votre équipe :"

#: ../../source/concepts/what-is-nexus-gateway.rst:54
msgid ""
"Runs three or more backend services that share authentication "
"requirements."
msgstr "Exploite trois services backend ou plus partageant des exigences d'authentification."

#: ../../source/concepts/what-is-nexus-gateway.rst:55
msgid "Needs fine-grained rate limiting per client, endpoint, or plan tier."
msgstr "A besoin d'une limitation de débit granulaire par client, point de terminaison ou niveau tarifaire."

#: ../../source/concepts/what-is-nexus-gateway.rst:56
msgid ""
"Wants a single place to manage routing rules without modifying service "
"code."
msgstr "Souhaite un endroit unique pour gérer les règles de routage sans modifier le code des services."

#: ../../source/concepts/what-is-nexus-gateway.rst:57
msgid "Requires audit logs of all API traffic for compliance purposes."
msgstr "Nécessite des journaux d'audit de tout le trafic API à des fins de conformité."

#: ../../source/concepts/what-is-nexus-gateway.rst:59
msgid ""
"If you are running a single service with straightforward access "
"requirements, a dedicated gateway may introduce unnecessary complexity. A"
" simple reverse proxy may be sufficient in that case."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/what-is-nexus-gateway.rst:64
msgid ""
"Nexus Gateway is not a service mesh. It handles north-south traffic "
"(client to service), not east-west traffic (service to service). For "
"east-west communication patterns, consider a service mesh such as Istio "
"or Linkerd alongside Nexus Gateway."
msgstr ""
